<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>It's so good to see the live entertainment world coming back to life post lockdown but, boy, are there some wacky shows coming up.</p>

<p>Camilla Kerslake, nicknamed the Scrummy Soprano thanks to her romance with former England rugby captain Chris Robshaw – is set to appear in a wrestling-themed production at the Cockpit Theatre and then the Playground Theatre in London this month. </p>

<p>Bread And Circuses is described as ‘a mash-up between World Wrestling Entertainment, verismo opera, and 1990s-style video-gaming’.</p>

<p>Owing to Covid-19 restrictions, performances run for just 20 minutes. Just as well – it all sounds exhausting!</p>

